summary:
I am a seasoned sales and strategic partnerships professional with over 8 years of experience in the technology and corporate sales sectors. Currently, I serve as the Corporate Account Executive for Spain and Portugal at DeepL, where I spearhead the company's growth and present our market-leading translation service to clients, while managing the entire sales cycle.

Before joining DeepL, I held the position of Account Executive at Faire, working on brand partnerships in France and contributing to cross-functional initiatives across multiple teams. I also gained significant experience at Dropbox, holding various roles including Enterprise Account Executive and Account Manager for France, Benelux, Spain, and Portugal.

I began my career in the technology sector as an Account Executive at Google, where I collaborated with regional teams of online advertising experts and helped scale processes, including sales training presentations and recruiting. Additionally, I have experience as a General Store Manager at Games Workshop Ltd, managing teams and implementing solutions to improve sales.

Throughout my career, I have demonstrated exceptional skills in sales, account management, strategic partnerships, and cross-functional collaboration. I have a proven track record of exceeding sales targets and developing solid relationships with clients and partners.
